'''Suzu no Gozen''' (鈴之御前社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Aichi Prefecture|ja|愛知県}}, {{ill|Nagoya|ja|名古屋市}}, {{ill|Atsuta Ward|ja|熱田区}}.

It is a subsidiary shrine ({{ill|Massha|ja|末社}}) of {{ill|Atsuta Shrine|ja|熱田神宮}}, with its enshrined deity being {{ill|Ame-no-Uzume-no-Mikoto|ja|天鈿女命}}. Locally, it is colloquially known as "Suzu no Miya" (鈴の宮). In the past, a river known as {{ill|Shinbori River (Nagoya)|ja|新堀川 (名古屋市)|lt=Shōjin River|lt_ja=精進川}} flowed near the shrine, and travelers along the {{ill|Tōkaidō|ja|東海道}} were required to receive a bell purification ritual at this shrine to cleanse themselves before visiting Atsuta.

After the war, it was relocated ({{ill|Relocation|ja|遷座}}) to its current site facing the former Tōkaidō.

From the subway station {{ill|Atsuta Shrine Denmachō Station|ja|熱田神宮伝馬町駅}}, if you proceed about 50 m to the southwest, you will reach the former {{ill|Tōkaidō|ja|東海道}} road. Continuing approximately 100 m toward the southeast, the shrine grounds will appear on your right. The grounds are only a few meters wide and are hard to spot from the national road.

== Annual Festival ==
Every year on {{ill|July 31|ja|7月31日}}, the shrine is known for its {{ill|Great Purification|ja|大祓|lt=Summer Purification|lt_ja=夏越しの祓}} (commonly known as the "Passing Through the Straw Ring" ritual).

== External Links ==
* [http://www.atsutajingu.or.jp/jingu/about/yukari/reinomimaesha.html Suzu no Gozen] (Atsuta Shrine official website)

