'''Suzu no Gozen''' (鈴之御前社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]], [[:en:Nagoya|Nagoya]], [[:en:Atsuta-ku, Nagoya|Atsuta Ward]].

It is a subsidiary shrine ({{ill|Massha|ja|末社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Massha|qq=}}) of [[:en:Atsuta Shrine|Atsuta Shrine]], with its enshrined deity being {{ill|Ame-no-Uzume|ja|天鈿女命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Uzume-no-Mikoto|qq=}}. Locally, it is colloquially known as "Suzu no Miya" (鈴の宮). In the past, a river known as {{ill|Shinbori River (Nagoya)|ja|新堀川 (名古屋市)|lt=Shōjin River|lt_ja=精進川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbori River (Nagoya)|qq=}} flowed near the shrine, and travelers along the [[:en:Tōkaidō (region)|Tōkaidō]] were required to receive a bell purification ritual at this shrine to cleanse themselves before visiting Atsuta.

After the war, it was relocated ({{ill|Relocation|ja|遷座|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Relocation|qq=}}) to its current site facing the former Tōkaidō.

From the subway station [[:en:Atsuta Jingu Temma-cho Station|Atsuta Shrine Denmachō Station]], if you proceed about 50 m to the southwest, you will reach the former [[:en:Tōkaidō (region)|Tōkaidō]] road. Continuing approximately 100 m toward the southeast, the shrine grounds will appear on your right. The grounds are only a few meters wide and are hard to spot from the national road.

== Annual Festival ==
Every year on [[:en:July 31|July 31]], the shrine is known for its [[:en:Ōharae-shiki|Summer Purification]] (commonly known as the "Passing Through the Straw Ring" ritual).

== External Links ==
* [http://www.atsutajingu.or.jp/jingu/about/yukari/reinomimaesha.html Suzu no Gozen] (Atsuta Shrine official website)

